1
00:01:30,220 --> 00:01:32,980
Episode 27

2
00:01:35,510 --> 00:01:36,280
Want some garlic?

3
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:39,510
Have some! It tastes nice!

4
00:01:39,790 --> 00:01:40,230
No.

5
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,070
I've been so busy that I haven't

6
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:46,150
had the time to see Mr. He off.

7
00:01:46,430 --> 00:01:47,150
It's fine.

8
00:01:48,040 --> 00:01:48,680
He said

9
00:01:48,870 --> 00:01:50,430
he'll book a flight for you two

10
00:01:50,590 --> 00:01:51,310
to go there

11
00:01:51,480 --> 00:01:52,280
for his 80th birthday.

12
00:01:52,480 --> 00:01:53,680
Oh my! That sounds good.

13
00:01:55,840 --> 00:01:57,040
Why isn't Qian here for the meal?

14
00:01:57,350 --> 00:01:59,000
Haven't seen her in days.

15
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:00,950
She's probably mad at me

16
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,920
for the argument we had.

17
00:02:02,590 --> 00:02:03,350
You two?

18
00:02:03,680 --> 00:02:04,280
No way.

19
00:02:04,840 --> 00:02:06,040
Maybe she found a new boyfriend

20
00:02:06,070 --> 00:02:07,040
and has no time for us.

21
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:09,560
That's more likely.

22
00:02:50,960 --> 00:02:52,190
What is it? Are you upset?

23
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:54,430
You're just a part-timer.

24
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,680
No need to come every day.

25
00:02:57,280 --> 00:02:57,680
Wait...

26
00:02:58,310 --> 00:02:59,470
Did I do something wrong?

27
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:01,680
You claim to be assisting with HR,

28
00:03:01,870 --> 00:03:03,280
but you chat with people every day.

29
00:03:03,960 --> 00:03:04,800
Don't bother others

30
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,120
just because you're bored,

31
00:03:06,190 --> 00:03:06,560
okay?

32
00:03:07,680 --> 00:03:08,520
No wonder you refused

33
00:03:08,560 --> 00:03:09,590
when I wanted to assign you

34
00:03:09,630 --> 00:03:10,430
your own office.

35
00:03:11,280 --> 00:03:12,560
To make chatting easier, huh?

36
00:03:12,800 --> 00:03:13,630
What?

37
00:03:14,190 --> 00:03:15,630
No, you misunderstood.

38
00:03:16,150 --> 00:03:16,840
I'm only

39
00:03:16,910 --> 00:03:19,000
helping our staff work better.

40
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:19,910
Besides, I only

41
00:03:19,960 --> 00:03:21,150
talk to them during tea breaks.

42
00:03:21,310 --> 00:03:22,240
And it's not chit-chat.

43
00:03:22,710 --> 00:03:23,280
Recently,

44
00:03:23,310 --> 00:03:24,710
the market has been very volatile.

45
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,190
Many employees have suffered

46
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,840
losses to varying degrees.

47
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:29,240
I only talked to them

48
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,310
to understand their situation,

49
00:03:30,430 --> 00:03:31,190
ease their emotions,

50
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,680
and avoid unnecessary risks.

51
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,080
What risks?

52
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:36,400
You really buy that?

53
00:03:36,960 --> 00:03:37,630
Fang Wanzhi,

54
00:03:37,870 --> 00:03:39,360
you have no idea about the stock market.

55
00:03:39,750 --> 00:03:40,680
A friend of mine

56
00:03:40,910 --> 00:03:41,750
had a mental breakdown

57
00:03:41,750 --> 00:03:42,400
and was hospitalized

58
00:03:42,470 --> 00:03:43,590
because he couldn't accept

59
00:03:43,680 --> 00:03:44,310
the losses.

60
00:03:44,470 --> 00:03:45,590
And some cases are even worse.

61
00:03:46,030 --> 00:03:47,190
But our company's employees

62
00:03:47,190 --> 00:03:48,030
are doing better.

63
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:49,360
Even those who bought stocks

64
00:03:49,430 --> 00:03:50,800
didn't stake all their assets

65
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,280
or use leverage.

66
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:53,800
Worse?

67
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:54,910
Worse how?

68
00:03:58,680 --> 00:03:59,710
Committing suicide.

69
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,030
I'll call her.

70
00:04:09,400 --> 00:04:09,960
Not answering.

71
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,520
Call whom?

72
00:04:12,150 --> 00:04:12,800
Do you have a copy

73
00:04:12,870 --> 00:04:13,520
of her key card?

74
00:04:13,520 --> 00:04:13,870
Yes.

75
00:04:14,120 --> 00:04:14,470
Let's go!

76
00:04:16,430 --> 00:04:17,480
What's wrong? Need my help?

77
00:04:17,870 --> 00:04:18,360
Come on.

78
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:32,510
The last time we saw her
was two weeks ago.

79
00:04:33,120 --> 00:04:34,360
She was definitely in a bad mood.

80
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:36,680
Stock trading...

81
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:37,680
All she knows is stocks.

82
00:04:37,800 --> 00:04:38,680
She's always claiming

83
00:04:38,750 --> 00:04:40,120
inside info, each bit worth 100 million.

84
00:04:40,510 --> 00:04:41,870
Isn't that just nonsense?

85
00:04:43,720 --> 00:04:45,040
I hope she's okay.

86
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:49,800
Qian?

87
00:04:58,920 --> 00:04:59,560
Qian!

88
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:13,800
Sleeping pills...

89
00:05:13,950 --> 00:05:14,600
Call an ambulance.

90
00:05:15,430 --> 00:05:15,920
Qian?

91
00:05:17,190 --> 00:05:17,680
Qian?

92
00:05:18,360 --> 00:05:19,160
Qian, talk to me.

93
00:05:19,240 --> 00:05:19,680
Qian?

94
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:21,360
Qian!

95
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:24,240
Why are you two here?

96
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,830
How many sleeping pills did you take?

97
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:29,600
If I had sleeping pills,

98
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,390
I wouldn't have lost sleep.

99
00:05:31,870 --> 00:05:33,680
I forgot to get a prescription.

100
00:05:33,750 --> 00:05:35,390
I didn't take any yesterday.

101
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,190
You scared me to death!

102
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:39,390
We thought you did something stupid!

103
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,070
Alright, relax.

104
00:05:46,950 --> 00:05:48,310
I wouldn't do that.

105
00:05:48,560 --> 00:05:50,240
I've been through too much

106
00:05:50,390 --> 00:05:51,560
to do stupid things.

107
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:53,360
We haven't seen you in two weeks.

108
00:05:53,480 --> 00:05:54,600
Li Juan and I were so worried,

109
00:05:54,680 --> 00:05:55,680
you know?

110
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,270
It feels so good to have friends

111
00:05:58,630 --> 00:05:59,240
who care.

112
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:07,160
Did you lose money on your stocks?

113
00:06:09,830 --> 00:06:10,480
How much?

114
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,800
Stop prying.

115
00:06:12,870 --> 00:06:14,600
The stock market
isn't doing well lately.

116
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:16,190
If I get the right information later,

117
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,190
I'll earn it all back.

118
00:06:17,190 --> 00:06:18,360
Stop being so stubborn now!

119
00:06:18,430 --> 00:06:19,950
This is what got you into trouble!

120
00:06:20,630 --> 00:06:22,190
Stop judging me now.

121
00:06:22,430 --> 00:06:23,390
I've thought about it.

122
00:06:23,630 --> 00:06:24,120
Because

123
00:06:24,120 --> 00:06:26,040
I kept going to your places for meals,

124
00:06:26,270 --> 00:06:27,600
and my place felt empty.

125
00:06:27,750 --> 00:06:29,390
That's why I lost money.

126
00:06:29,870 --> 00:06:31,070
So it's our fault?

127
00:06:32,390 --> 00:06:33,310
It's settled then.

128
00:06:33,430 --> 00:06:35,160
Come over for dinner this weekend

129
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,360
and add some warmth to my home.

130
00:06:37,560 --> 00:06:39,480
Then, my stocks might rise.

131
00:06:54,240 --> 00:06:55,190
Ignore that. Go straight!

132
00:06:55,310 --> 00:06:56,160
Go! Straight ahead!

133
00:06:56,390 --> 00:06:57,040
Go straight!

134
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:57,750
Go forward!

135
00:06:57,870 --> 00:06:58,950
Pedal to the metal!

136
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,190
Hao Qianqian, go!

137
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,830
Yes! Keep it up!

138
00:07:03,310 --> 00:07:04,240
Oh, no! Stop!

139
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,680
To the right! Yes!

140
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:06,830
Don't go that way!

141
00:07:07,720 --> 00:07:09,070
What is that about?

142
00:07:09,190 --> 00:07:10,190
I don't want to play.

143
00:07:10,830 --> 00:07:12,600
Gao Xiang said this was
exciting and would help

144
00:07:12,920 --> 00:07:13,680
release stress.

145
00:07:13,750 --> 00:07:14,830
That's why I bought one.

146
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:16,830
I knew it was him.

147
00:07:17,120 --> 00:07:17,920
Let me tell you,

148
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,680
he's just so clueless.

149
00:07:19,870 --> 00:07:21,310
If he were a little more sensible,

150
00:07:21,510 --> 00:07:23,120
he'd have won you over long ago.

151
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,000
Still saying that?

152
00:07:25,310 --> 00:07:25,950
You're fine.

153
00:07:27,160 --> 00:07:28,070
Alright, lunch's ready.

154
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:28,560
Stop playing.

155
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:29,600
Okay.

156
00:07:29,830 --> 00:07:30,240
Let's eat.

157
00:07:33,920 --> 00:07:34,720
Gao Xiang...

158
00:07:35,360 --> 00:07:36,120
I didn't invite him.

159
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,950
It must be Juan.

160
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:38,800
I didn't, either.

161
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:40,510
Welcome...

162
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,190
I...

163
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:52,800
Qian!

164
00:07:52,830 --> 00:07:53,240
Zhu,

165
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:54,360
step back.

166
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,430
No, Qian.

167
00:07:57,070 --> 00:07:58,240
I didn't want to come...

168
00:07:58,720 --> 00:07:59,120
But...

169
00:07:59,360 --> 00:07:59,950
Enough.

170
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:05,070
Stop yelling.

171
00:08:14,870 --> 00:08:15,600
Dahu.

172
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:18,510
He wants

173
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:21,120
to see his mother.

174
00:08:21,950 --> 00:08:23,270
Dahu's grown so tall?

175
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,120
Dad,

176
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:27,560
I saw her.

177
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:28,600
Let's go now.

178
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:29,270
Hey, you brat!

179
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:30,920
How can you be so rude?

180
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,670
This is Ms. Fang

181
00:08:36,320 --> 00:08:37,510
and Ms. Li.

182
00:08:37,750 --> 00:08:39,360
They're your mom's best friends.

183
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:40,790
You came to Shenzhen

184
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:42,240
for the New Year once as a child,

185
00:08:42,750 --> 00:08:43,360
and they both

186
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:44,480
gave you a gift!

187
00:08:48,910 --> 00:08:49,790
His mother...

188
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,240
She didn't even get to see Dahu.

189
00:08:56,630 --> 00:08:57,600
Dahu came?

190
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:00,550
Why didn't I see him?

191
00:09:00,550 --> 00:09:01,390
Where is he hiding?

192
00:09:09,150 --> 00:09:10,320
I won't see Liu Zhu.

193
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:12,840
But I need to see Dahu.

194
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,120
Help me bring him in here.

195
00:09:29,390 --> 00:09:30,030
Zhu,

196
00:09:30,910 --> 00:09:31,480
have a seat.

197
00:09:32,120 --> 00:09:32,720
Oh, please.

198
00:09:33,270 --> 00:09:35,000
Stop calling me that.

199
00:09:35,630 --> 00:09:37,200
You're a big businesswoman now.

200
00:09:37,720 --> 00:09:39,440
I used to work at your canteen.

201
00:09:40,600 --> 00:09:41,080
Sit down.

202
00:09:45,550 --> 00:09:46,390
Just put it there.

203
00:10:00,320 --> 00:10:01,600
How did you find this place?

204
00:10:05,510 --> 00:10:06,910
Actually, I've known she lived here

205
00:10:06,910 --> 00:10:07,720
for a long time.

206
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,720
If Dahu wanted to see his mother,

207
00:10:10,870 --> 00:10:12,030
I had to find her, right?

208
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:15,030
Didn't you promise not

209
00:10:15,510 --> 00:10:16,600
to disturb Qian again?

210
00:10:17,120 --> 00:10:17,840
Yes.

211
00:10:18,440 --> 00:10:19,080
And I won't.

212
00:10:20,200 --> 00:10:21,870
I really had no choice this time.

213
00:10:22,750 --> 00:10:24,120
My mom passed away.

214
00:10:24,480 --> 00:10:25,390
Dahu is filial.

215
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:26,390
He was very sad,

216
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,000
which affected his
college entrance exam.

217
00:10:28,630 --> 00:10:29,550
He insisted on finding

218
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:30,200
a job in Shenzhen

219
00:10:30,670 --> 00:10:32,320
instead of going to a vocational school.

220
00:10:34,030 --> 00:10:34,630
I know

221
00:10:37,030 --> 00:10:38,360
he just wants to see

222
00:10:40,670 --> 00:10:41,360
his mother.

223
00:10:50,240 --> 00:10:51,840
I actually gave birth

224
00:10:53,550 --> 00:10:54,630
to a son this tall?

225
00:10:55,750 --> 00:10:56,630
I didn't expect you

226
00:10:58,750 --> 00:10:59,720
to still look so young.

227
00:11:01,270 --> 00:11:02,630
You're prettier than I imagined.

228
00:11:10,030 --> 00:11:11,000
You look handsome.

229
00:11:12,120 --> 00:11:13,440
I don't remember much about you.

230
00:11:14,670 --> 00:11:15,670
Grandpa threw away

231
00:11:17,120 --> 00:11:18,150
all your photos at home.

232
00:11:20,550 --> 00:11:21,320
But I know

233
00:11:24,150 --> 00:11:25,390
my mom must look very pretty.

234
00:11:27,750 --> 00:11:28,910
I probably look like my mom.

235
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:31,840
I know

236
00:11:32,510 --> 00:11:33,630
you gave Dad quite a big sum.

237
00:11:35,270 --> 00:11:36,360
You don't need to care for me.

238
00:11:37,910 --> 00:11:38,550
So,

239
00:11:40,320 --> 00:11:41,030
I'll be going.

240
00:11:55,750 --> 00:11:56,270
Mom,

241
00:11:59,150 --> 00:11:59,790
goodbye.

242
00:12:01,630 --> 00:12:02,390
Dahu...

243
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:09,600
Dahu...

244
00:12:15,670 --> 00:12:17,150
My child...

245
00:12:21,720 --> 00:12:23,030
My son...

246
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,270
Should I warm up the food?

247
00:12:42,870 --> 00:12:43,720
Wait a bit longer.

248
00:12:53,480 --> 00:12:54,150
What's your plan

249
00:12:54,440 --> 00:12:55,150
for this trip?

250
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,320
I want to stay and work.

251
00:12:57,960 --> 00:12:58,750
What about your dad?

252
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,510
He set me up on two more dates.

253
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:04,790
I refused both.

254
00:13:05,120 --> 00:13:06,600
My dad was mad and called me a coward.

255
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:07,910
He moved

256
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:09,320
to my elder brother's place.

257
00:13:09,670 --> 00:13:11,670
Back home, Dahu and I...

258
00:13:15,200 --> 00:13:15,790
Well...

259
00:13:17,150 --> 00:13:18,030
No one cares for him.

260
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,440
Ms. Fang.

261
00:13:26,720 --> 00:13:27,320
Ms. Li.

262
00:13:27,840 --> 00:13:28,870
My mom wants you to eat first.

263
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:30,790
You're not eating?

264
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:31,480
We are.

265
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,270
Ms. Li, please prepare two plates

266
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,030
of food

267
00:13:34,670 --> 00:13:35,510
for us to eat inside.

268
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:43,840
May... Maybe...

269
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:44,670
I should go.

270
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:46,480
Enjoy your meal.

271
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:47,550
No.

272
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:49,720
Qian's right.

273
00:13:50,270 --> 00:13:51,510
They haven't met for years.

274
00:13:51,670 --> 00:13:53,080
Let them have some private time.

275
00:13:53,670 --> 00:13:54,550
Juan and I will go

276
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:55,720
get you some food.

277
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,000
About that...

278
00:14:02,440 --> 00:14:03,320
What's your mom's opinion?

279
00:14:04,840 --> 00:14:05,840
She doesn't want me to work.

280
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,510
She wants me to study here.

281
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:10,270
Don't worry about that.

282
00:14:12,480 --> 00:14:13,030
Fine.

283
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,630
I'll stay in Shenzhen.

284
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,480
Just call me if you need anything.

285
00:14:17,270 --> 00:14:18,240
I'll find a job tomorrow.

286
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:20,600
Alright, Dahu.

287
00:14:21,200 --> 00:14:21,630
Let's go.

288
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:22,510
Go in and eat.

289
00:14:34,320 --> 00:14:35,150
Forget about job hunting.

290
00:14:37,030 --> 00:14:38,440
Come work at my toy factory's canteen.

291
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,270
Aren't you afraid I'll act up?

292
00:14:46,150 --> 00:14:47,840
I know your character.

293
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,840
I know you only acted on impulse

294
00:14:50,200 --> 00:14:50,870
back then.

295
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:52,390
After leaving that canteen,

296
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:53,320
I've never seen

297
00:14:53,440 --> 00:14:55,200
a pastry chef as good as you.

298
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,120
Have you gotten rusty?

299
